ijing%20decides%20to%20try%20and%20take%20over.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20China%20does%20invade%2C%20Taiwanese%20officials%20and%20cybersecurity%20experts%20say%20it%20will%20not%20limit%20its%20assaults%20to%20security%20forces%20and%20defence%20infrastructure%2C%20but%20effectively%20disconnect%20the%20island%20from%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETaiwan%20is%20facing%20a%20persistent%20threat%20from%20stealthy%20attackers%20who%20gain%20access%20to%20computer%20networks%20to%20%26quot%3Bsit%20and%20wait%20within%20the%20victim's%20infrastructure%26quot%3B%2C%20said%20Crystal%20Tu%2C%20a%20cybersecurity%20researcher%20at%20Taiwan's%20Institute%20of%20National%20Defense%20and%20Security%20Research.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20can%20be%20highly%20active%20during%20a%20time%20of%20conflict%2C%20Tu%20told%20AFP%2C%20such%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bcyber%20operation%20aimed%20at%20the%20disruption%20of%20critical%20infrastructure%20--%20including%20telecommunications%2C%20energy%20and%20finance%20sectors%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECyberattacks%20against%20Taiwan%20have%20ramped%20up%20dramatically%20in%20the%20year%20leading%20up%20to%20the%20presidential%20election%20on%20Saturday%2C%20which%20China%20has%20described%20as%20a%20choice%20between%20war%20and%20peace%20for%20the%20island's%2023%20million%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETaiwanese%20authorities%20have%20said%20government%20agencies%20face%20an%20estimated%20five%20million%20cyberattacks%20a%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20the%20cybersecurity%20firm%20Fortinet%20reported%20an%2080%20percent%20increase%20in%20cyber%20attacks%20in%20the%20first%20half%20of%202023%20--%20ranking%20Taiwan%20number%20one%20in%20Asia%20Pacific.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20cyber%20operation%20toward%20Taiwan%20never%20really%20stops%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Tu.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20tactics%20used%20against%20Taiwanese%20infrastructure%20have%20been%20identified%20as%20techniques%20used%20by%20Chinese%20state-sponsored%20groups.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20Microsoft%20flagged%20the%20threat%20from%20a%20group%20named%20Flax%20Typhoon%20that%20operates%20out%20of%20China%20and%20targets%20Taiwan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20tech%20giant%20said%20Flax%20Typhoon%20%26quot%3Bintends%20to%20perform%20espionage%20and%20maintain%20access%26quot%3B%20to%20various%20Taiwanese%20organisations%20for%20as%20long%20as%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESemiconductor%20hub%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECyberattackers%20have%20not%20only%20targeted%20Taiwan's%20government%20and%20defence%20organisations%2C%20but%20also%20hit%20its%20semiconductor%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETaiwanese%20companies%20are%20crucial%20to%20the%20supply%20of%20chips%2C%20the%20lifeblood%20of%20the%20global%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuch%20is%20their%20importance%20that%20one%20former%20US%20official%20said%20last%20year%20that%20the%20United%20States%20would%20rather%20destroy%20this%20semiconductor%20infrastructure%20than%20let%20it%20fall%20to%20invading%20Chinese%20forces.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20the%20Taiwan%20Semiconductor%20Manufacturing%20Company%20(TSMC)%2C%20which%20controls%20more%20than%20half%20of%20the%20world's%20chip%20output%2C%20reported%20a%20data%20breach%20at%20one%20of%20its%20suppliers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTaiwan%20is%20an%20important%20target%20because%20it%20is%20at%20the%20top%20of%20the%20critical%20high-tech%20supply%20chain%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Fortinet's%20Jim%20Liu.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGeopolitics%20and%20(China-Taiwan)%20relations%20could%20inevitably%20increase%20cybersecurity%20incidents.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina%20has%20increased%20diplomatic%20and%20military%20pressure%20on%20the%20island%20since%202016%2C%20when%20Tsai%20Ing-wen%20of%20the%20Democratic%20Progressive%20Party%20became%20Taiwan's%20president.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20considers%20Taiwan%20an%20independent%20state%20and%20does%20not%20accept%20China's%20claim%20on%20the%20island%20--%20views%20shared%20by%20Lai%20Ching-te%2C%20the%20DPP's%20presidential%20candidate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWorst-case%20scenario%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina's%20increasing%20aggression%20towards%20Taiwan%2C%20including%20simulated%20blockades%20of%20the%20island%2C%20has%20fuelled%20speculation%20among%20policymakers%20about%20Beijing's%20potential%20timeline%20--%20and%20methods%20--%20for%20an%20invasion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20digital%20realm%2C%20Taiwanese%20officials%20say%20China%20could%20go%20beyond%20cyberattacks%20and%20effectively%20cut%20off%20the%20island%20from%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBecause%20Taiwan%20is%20an%20island%2C%20all%20communication%20with%20the%20outside%20world%20relies%20on%20undersea%20cables%2C%26quot%3B%20Taiwan's%20deputy%20digital%20minister%20Huai-jen%20Lee%20told%20AFP%20in%20a%20recent%20interview.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20worst-case%20scenario%20is%20all%20our%20undersea%20cables%20are%20cut%20off.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20prepare%20for%20that%2C%20Taiwan%20is%20looking%20to%20the%20sky.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDeputy%20Digital%20Minister%20Lee%20told%20AFP%20that%20Taiwan%20is%20working%20with%20two%20foreign%20satellite%20service%20providers%20to%20collaborate%20with%20the%20island's%20largest%20telecom%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESatellite%20receivers%20will%20be%20placed%20in%20700%20spots%20across%20Taiwan%20%26quot%3Bto%20test%20whether%20we%20can%20switch%20communication%20systems%26quot%3B%20during%20times%20of%20crisis%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20first%20thing...%20is%20to%20maintain%20the%20stability%20of%20the%20government's%20command%20system%20and%20maintain%20the%20accuracy%20of%20the%20information%20provided%26quot%3B%20to%20civilians%2C%20he%20told%20AFP.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndic