oving%20on%20after%20cheating%20is%20hard%20%E2%80%94%20even%20if%20you're%20the%20one%20who%20had%20an%20affair%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Doing%20It%20Right%20Series%3A%20Infidelity%20leads%20to%20conflicts%20and%20un%20fulfilling%20relationship%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F659c10166979d73718213903%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIf%20you%20don't%20take%20time%20to%20process%20all%20of%20the%20reasons%20why%20your%20relationship%20didn't%20work%20out%2C%20you%20could%20get%20stuck%20in%20a%20shame%20spiral%2C%20therapist%20Leanna%20Stockard%20said.%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3B%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EIf%20you%20enter%20a%20new%20relationship%20without%20processing%20your%20last%20one%2C%20it%20could%20catch%20up%20with%20you.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EA%20therapist%20said%20feelings%20of%20remorse%20and%20shame%20can%20be%20hard%20to%20face%2C%20but%20doing%20so%20can%20lead%20to%20closure.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20suggested%20reflecting%20on%20your%20past%20and%20avoiding%20black-and-white%20thinking.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22doing%20it%20right%20banner%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5d81117ff4fc2402cd7a53d9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22151%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ESamantha%20Lee%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDear%20Julia%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThree%20years%20ago%2C%20I%20cheated%20on%20my%20then-boyfriend.%20Now%2C%20I'm%20in%20a%20loving%20relationship%20with%20the%20man%20I%20cheated%20on%20him%20with%2C%20but%20I%20still%20can't%20get%20my%20ex%20out%20of%20my%20head.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20man%20I%20cheated%20with%20had%20been%20a%20previous%20fling%20but%20I%20felt%20so%20guilty%20about%20what%20I%20had%20done.%20I%20came%20clean%20to%20my%20boyfriend%20and%20fought%20hard%20to%20try%20to%20save%20our%20relationship.%20But%20our%20dynamic%20became%20toxic%20and%20my%20boyfriend%20broke%20up%20with%20me%20a%20year%20later.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%3Cem%3EWhen%20I%20heard%20that%20he%20had%20started%20to%20date%20someone%20new%2C%20I%20reached%20back%20out%20to%20the%20man%20I%20had%20cheated%20with.%20He%20still%20lived%20nearby%2C%20and%20I%20couldn't%20stop%20thinking%20about%20him.%20The%20attraction%20was%20still%20there%2C%20and%20we%20hit%20it%20off%20just%20like%20we%20did%20three%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESoon%20after%20my%20new%20relationship%20became%20official%2C%20I%20heard%20through%20mutual%20friends%20that%20my%20ex%20was%20unhappy%20about%20it%20and%20that%20he%20thought%20of%20my%20new%20beau%20as%20his%20biggest%20insecurity.%20Since%20hearing%20this%20news%2C%20I%20can't%20stop%20thinking%20about%20my%20ex%20and%20that%20there%20might%20be%20a%20chance%20to%20be%20with%20him.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EI'm%20so%20confused.%20I%20love%20my%20current%20partner%2C%20but%20worry%20that%20I%20didn't%20take%20the%20time%20to%20fully%20mourn%20the%20heartbreak%20of%20my%20previous%20relationship.%20What%20should%20I%20do%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E-%20Virginia%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDear%20Virginia%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20sorry%20you%20feel%20unsettled%20by%20thoughts%20about%20your%20ex-boyfriend.%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frebound-relationship-last-therapist-advice-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20%3Cu%3EMoving%20on%20from%20a%20relationship%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20never%20easy%2C%20especially%20when%20it%20was%20not%20your%20choice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20there's%20nothing%20wrong%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsigns-rebound-relationship-unhealthy-according-therapist-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eseeking%20connection%20following%20a%20breakup%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20diving%20into%20a%20fresh%20relationship%20before%20processing%20your%20previous%20one%20can%20make%20it%20difficult%20to%20be%20fully%20present%20with%20a%20new%20partner%2C%20Leanna%20Stockard%2C%20a%20therapist%20who%20specializes%20in%20repairing%20broken%20trust%20in%20relationships%2C%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20that%20learning%20to%20face%20lingering%20feelings%20of%20guilt%2C%20shame%2C%20and%20confusion%20due%20to%20your%20past%20infidelity%20can%20help%20you%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fwired-to-cheat-agreed-to-marriage-will-i-ruin-it-2020-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eshed%20self-judgment%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20understand%20why%20you%20acted%20in%20ways%20you%20may%20now%20regret.%20This%20process%20can%20help%20someone%20forgive%20themself%2C%20which%20is%20essential%20for%20having%20healthy%20relationships%20in%20the%20future%2C%20said%20Stockard.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20impossible%20to%20control%20whether%20someone%20else%20forgives%20you%2C%20even%20if%20you%20apologize.%20But%20you%20can%20always%20learn%20to%20forgive%20yourself%2C%20which%20will%20in%20turn%20limit%20any%20temptation%20your%20brain%20might%20have%20to%20fixate%20on%20past%20love.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EReflect%20on%20why%20you%20cheated%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20may%20sound%20counterintuitive%2C%20but%20to%20stop%20fixating%20on%20your%20relationship%20with%20your%20ex%2C%20you%20must%20think%20deeply%20about%20your%20relationship%20with%20him%2C%20Stockard%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20that%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fwired-to-cheat-agreed-to-marriage-will-i-ruin-it-2020-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20%3Cu%3Eunderstanding%20why%20you%20cheated%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20why%20your%20relationship%20felt%20toxic%2C%20could%20help%20you%20feel%20a%20sense%20of%20closure%2C%20especially%20if%20you%20feel%20like%20you%20didn't%20fully%20mourn%20the%20relationship%20when%20it%20ended.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Stockard%2C%20it's%20important%20to%20consider%20how%20past%20experiences%20and%20your%20dynamic%20with%20your%20partner%20contributed%20to%20your%20decision%20to%20step%20out%20on%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-your-parents-behaviors-shape-who-you-are-today-2019-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDive%20deeper%20into%20those%20past%20experiences%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20how%20your%20current%20situation%20and%20environment%20might%20have%20encouraged%20you%20to%20make%20those%20mistakes%20or%20engage%20in%20those%20behaviors%20you%20learned.%20Try%20to%20understand%20the%20why%2C%26quot%3B%20Stockard%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%2C%20for%20example%2C%20someone%20learned%20from%20a%20young%20age%20that%20being%20emotionally%20guarded%20was%20safer%20than%20being%20vulnerable%20during%20tough%20moments%2C%20then%20they%20might%20self-sabotage%20their%20relationship%20when%20they%20feel%20uncomfortably%20close%20to%20a%20partner%2C%20Stockard%20explained%20to%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20focused%20on%20just%20the%20cheating%20in%20that%20one%20situation%2C%20you're%20not%20going%20to%20get%20a%20full%2C%20clear%20picture%20as%20to%20why%20you%20did%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Stockard%20said.%20And%20without%20that%20full%20picture%2C%20it%20will%20be%20more%20difficult%20to%20learn%20and%20grow%20from%20your%20missteps.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20you%20start%20to%20do%20this%2C%20Stockard%20suggested%20telling%20your%20current%20boyfriend%20that%20you%20need%20some%20time%20to%20figure%20out%20some%20complicated%20emotions%20you're%20feeling.%20Express%20to%20him%20that%20you%20want%20to%20share%20the%20details%2C%20but%20first%2C%20you%20need%20to%20think%20about%20it%20yourself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20approach%20allows%20for%20transparency%2C%20while%20also%20ensuring%20your%20current%20partner's%20perspective%20on%20the%20situation%20doesn't%20interfere%20with%20your%20personal%20process.%20And%2C%20if%20you%20seem%20more%20distant%20than%20usual%2C%20he'll%20know%20why%20that%20is%2C%20according%20to%20Stockard.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20may%20not%20be%20able%20to%20be%20fully%20present%20with%20your%20current%20partner%20while%20you%20do%20this%2C%20but%20that's%20a%20short-term%20consequence%20for%20the%20long-term%20benefit%20of%20being%20fully%20over%20your%20ex%2C%20Stockard%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ERemember%20that%20cheating%20doesn't%20have%20to%20define%20you%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20you%20consider%20how%20your%20upbringing%2C%20previous%20relationships%2C%20and%20worldview%20have%20contributed%20to%20your%20dynamics%20with%20partners%2C%20you%20may%20have%20a%20lingering%20feeling%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fhow-to-let-go-of-secrets-causing-you-shame2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eguilt%20for%20how%20you%20behaved%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20according%20to%20Stockard.%20Or%2C%20you%20may%20feel%20the%20urge%20to%20avoid%20taking%20any%20responsibility%20for%20what%20happened.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20notice%20these%20thoughts%20and%20feelings%2C%20it's%20important%20to%20remind%20yourself%20how%20complex%20relationships%20are%20in%20order%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fmental-health%2Fcognitive-bias%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eavoid%20black-and-white%20thinking%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Stockard%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20needs%20to%20be%20a%20sense%20of%20forgiveness%20for%20yourself%2C%20and%20recognition%20that%20we're%20human%20beings%20and%20humans%20make%20mistakes.%20But%20mistakes%20don't%20define%20our%20lives%2C%20and%20they%20don't%20necessarily%20determine%20all%20future%20actions%2C%26quot%3B%20Stockard%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAs%20Insider's%20resident%20sex%20and%20relatio